'''Number Assignment Module (NAM)''' - The NAM is the [[Memory card|electronic memory]] in the [[cellular phone]] that stores the [[telephone number]], [[International mobile subscriber identity]] and an [[Electronic Serial Number]]. Phones with dual- or multi-NAM features offer users the option of registering the phone with a local number in more than one market.

