In [[digital circuit]]s, '''propagation time''' is the delay of the basic inverter of a given [[logic family|family]]. Thus, it measures the speed at which such family can operate.<ref>Adel Sedra, ''Microelectronics Circuits'', Oxford University Press, New York, 1988, {{ISBN|970-613-379-8}} </ref>
